SIMPLE: retrieve
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Retrieve
<hw>Re*trieve"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Retrieved</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Retrieving</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>retreven</ets>, OF. <ets>retrover</ets> to find again, recover
(<ets>il retroeve</ets>e finds again), F. <ets>retrouver</ets>; pref.
<ets>re-</ets> re- + OF. <ets>trover</ets> to find, F.
<ets>trouver</ets>. See <er>Trover</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To find
again; to recover; to regain; to restore from loss or injury; <as>as, to
<ex>retrieve</ex> one's character; to <ex>retrieve</ex>
independence</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With late repentance now they would <qex>retrieve</qex>⟦br⟧
The bodies they forsook, and wish to live.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To recall; to bring back.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To <qex>retrieve</qex> them from their cold, trivial conceits.</q>
<rj><qau>Berkeley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1232 --></p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To remedy the evil consequence of, to repair, as a
loss or damadge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Accept my sorrow, and <qex>retrieve</qex> my fall.</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There is much to be done . . . and much to be
<qex>retrieved</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To recover; regain; recruit; repair;
restore.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Retrieve</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Retrieve
<hw>Re*trieve"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <fld>(Sport.)</fld>
<def>To discover and bring in game that has been killed or wounded;
<as>as, a dog naturally inclined to <ex>retrieve</ex></as>.</def>
<rj><au>Walsh.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Retrieve</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Retrieve
<hw>Re*trieve"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A seeking again; a
discovery.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The recovery of game once sprung; -- an old sporting
term.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Nares.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Retrievement</ent>⟦br⟧
